	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Listen to this one,<BR>
This spell rocks in pvp, or any duel against  Necros.  At level 22 I dueled a 29 necro, cast this spell on his pet and Bye Bye, I repeat bye bye. This spell works so good at Duels, we own necro in duels.  With out their pet, they are nothing (that is against us).<BR>
We have all the spells to counter their dots, and more mana then they can deal with, even better at 24 with 300 hp heal.  Cast Divine aura after their pet is gone and watch them mana dumb.  I don&#8217;t care if they read this or not, their pets are bye bye.<BR>
And since I am on the topic about dueling I will let you all in on some tips, if you don&#8217;t know about them already.  If you are lower level travel to the George maze and find the Humorous Mace (spelling may be off) although the damage is not great the delay is constant interrupt against casters.  <BR>
<BR>
The embed black mace is true faster but not very obtainable at lower level.<BR>
Another tip, in dueling don&#8217;t use stun, use either furor or strike, It does the same thing as stun pretty much, as far as interrupting there cast, as soon as you see them start casting cast strike 12 mana (ohh that a big waste :) ), and bammo opponents spell fizzles.  I prefer strike, what an awesome cast time, and you can cast it after they begin to cast and still keep them interrupted.<BR>
<BR>
One more of many but I will not waste no more space.<BR>
I know this seems like a big suggestion but o well<BR>
Jboots need I say more.  As soon as you can camp these, get them.  All the spells that you may think are useless, well you will find new uses in them with the boots.<BR>
<BR>
A kiting cleric, how awesome.  I kite yellow gnolls and some red gnolls (reds if I have a clarity).  I know I am only Mid 20's right now but I have been playing for a while.<BR>
Sure clerics don&#8217;t have the best dd spells or dot spells, but man we rock.<BR>
<BR>
Torement,<BR>
<BR>
This information is probably in the wrong place but I took advantage of telling the uses of SPOOK the DEAD.  O I am sure once this becomes used more;  All the necros are going to start crying.  <BR>
I repeat bye bye.<BR>
